<b><font class="print-title">EqLuclin links tip - link updates and broken links</font></b><br /><br />
<font class="print-sub">Articles / Luclin News<br />
<b>Date:</b> Nov 25, 2003 - 06:16 PM</font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal">This always seems confusing to folks, and I will make a short FAQ on it for the FAQ section. However, for best results when reporting a broken link, a new link, or a link modification always be logged in (so we have some indication you're a creditable person). Next, for each case:<br>
<br>
 - <b>1.</b> If you're adding a new link, add it as usual.<br>
 - <b>2.</b> If you'd like a link or description changed (especially for a guild), go to that link and click &quot;Modify&quot;.<br>
 - <b>3.</b> If there's a link that no longer works (for whatever reason), only then click the &quot;Report Broken Link&quot; option. If a broken link report shows up from someone who's not logged in, it will most likely be ignored. <br>
 - <b>4.</b> If you're from a guild that has been disbanded and you want the link deleted (or you want it deleted for some other reason), please make that clear on the boards (or via e-mail) as it's a separate case entirely.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps. We're running a link verifications every now and then to make sure that all links (guilds and other) are at least pointing at something valid, to try to keep the content as accurate as possible. Tymmon put the functionality in here, might as well use it!<br>
<br>
~Bic<br /><br />
<br />
</font>
</td></tr>
